                            <comment id="446064" author="adilger" created="Thu, 27 Feb 2025 17:10:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is related to the patches you have submitted on &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18332&quot; title=&quot;lfs migrate is not setting the mirror count&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18332&quot;&gt;LU-18332&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="445539" author="adilger" created="Mon, 24 Feb 2025 16:55:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve filed &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18746&quot; title=&quot;&amp;#39;lfs mirror extend&amp;#39; should allow creating a new STALE mirror&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18746&quot;&gt;LU-18746&lt;/a&gt; to allow creating a new file with the &lt;tt&gt;STALE&lt;/tt&gt; flag, which will need mostly the same functionality on the MDS.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="438800" author="adilger" created="Mon, 16 Dec 2024 16:31:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;it would also be useful to have an option like &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs mirror extend --no-resync&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; for adding &lt;b&gt;only&lt;/b&gt; the STALE mirror component(s) to a file&apos;s layout without trying to do any data resync on the file.  That can be used to add the mirror layout with specific parameters, and then offload the data resync to another node/process without the complexity of having to pass the layout. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
